Therefore, the velocity you
will actually measure is

00:28:46.717 --> 00:28:49.670
somewhat bigger than what I
expected in the old days.

00:28:49.670 --> 00:28:53.039
If you ever want to get back to
the good old days in any

00:28:53.039 --> 00:28:56.408
relativistic calculation,
you should let the velocity of

00:28:56.408 --> 00:28:59.390
light go to infinity.
Of course, it's not infinity.

00:28:59.390 --> 00:29:03.094
What you really mean is
u/c and v/c are

00:29:03.094 --> 00:29:05.200
negligible.
That means my velocity,

00:29:05.200 --> 00:29:07.716
the bullet velocity,
they're all small compared to

00:29:07.716 --> 00:29:11.071
the velocity of light;
we get back the answer from the

00:29:11.071 --> 00:29:13.038
old days.
This is the answer from the new

00:29:13.038 --> 00:29:13.290
days.

00:29:17.450 --> 00:29:21.190
Now, let's find the beauty of
this result.

00:29:21.190 --> 00:29:26.281
Let's get the reverse result.
Let us solve for the velocity I

00:29:26.281 --> 00:29:29.740
get in terms of the velocity you
get.

00:29:29.740 --> 00:29:32.734
Again, I think you realize you
can do the algebra,

00:29:32.734 --> 00:29:36.279
but you guys should know that
to go from me back to you,

00:29:36.279 --> 00:29:39.030
I should simply reverse the
sign of the relative velocity.

00:29:44.420 --> 00:29:46.529
This is the backwards result.
In other words,

00:29:46.529 --> 00:29:49.809
you're in a train and you fired
a bullet towards the front of

00:29:49.809 --> 00:29:52.799
the train.
What speed do I attribute to

00:29:52.799 --> 00:29:56.578
the bullet from the ground?
Well, I add the bullet speed to

00:29:56.578 --> 00:29:59.119
the train speed.
That's what the numerator is.

00:29:59.119 --> 00:30:02.591
The numerator says the answer
is somewhat less than that by

00:30:02.591 --> 00:30:04.369
this number.
Yes?

00:30:04.369 --> 00:30:07.545
Student:
[inaudible]

00:30:07.545 --> 00:30:13.530
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Thank you very

00:30:13.530 --> 00:30:18.250
much.
Yeah.

00:30:18.250 --> 00:30:21.982
That's absolutely correct.
What I really need to do--quite

00:30:21.982 --> 00:30:25.259
correct--it's not simply to
change u to -u,

00:30:25.259 --> 00:30:28.578
but to change the velocities
that you were seeing and put

00:30:28.578 --> 00:30:31.660
them in the place of velocities
that I was seeing.

00:30:31.660 --> 00:30:36.400
That's correct.
This is what you want to get.

00:30:36.400 --> 00:30:40.950
Now, let's look at the strength
of this result.

00:30:40.950 --> 00:30:43.322
If someone tells you according
to relatively,

00:30:43.322 --> 00:30:45.749
nothing can go faster than the
speed of light,

00:30:45.749 --> 00:30:48.230
you can try to beat the system
as follows.

00:30:48.230 --> 00:30:51.255
You can come to me and say,
"Can there be a gun whose

00:30:51.255 --> 00:30:54.339
bullets go at three-fourths the
velocity of light?"

00:30:54.339 --> 00:30:56.066
and I would say,
"yes," and you'd say,

00:30:56.066 --> 00:30:58.866
"How about a train that goes at
three-fourths the velocity of

00:30:58.866 --> 00:31:00.455
light?"
and I would say that seems to

00:31:00.455 --> 00:31:01.830
be allowed.
Then you can say,

00:31:01.830 --> 00:31:04.732
"Well, let me get into this
train at three-fourths the

00:31:04.732 --> 00:31:07.743
velocity of light and fire a
bullet at three-fourths the

00:31:07.743 --> 00:31:10.166
velocity,
then from the ground it should

00:31:10.166 --> 00:31:13.259
appear to be going at 1.5 times
the velocity of light."

00:31:13.259 --> 00:31:15.400
Well, that's the naive
expectation.

00:31:15.400 --> 00:31:19.848
But if you do it now,
let's put w = ¾c

00:31:19.848 --> 00:31:24.640
and u = ¾c,
the old answer is disaster;

00:31:24.640 --> 00:31:28.790
it says 1.5c,
but the correct answer is that

00:31:28.790 --> 00:31:30.700
plus (¾)^(2).

00:31:37.720 --> 00:31:46.089
So, what is this guy?
This is 1.5c divided by

00:31:46.089 --> 00:31:48.180
1 + 9/16.

00:31:52.730 --> 00:31:56.738
You multiply everything by 16.
On the top you'll get 24,

00:31:56.738 --> 00:32:00.230
the bottom will get 25 [times]
c.

00:32:00.230 --> 00:32:04.953
You see, you can jack up the
velocity as seen by the ground

00:32:04.953 --> 00:32:07.812
but it'll never be 1.5.
It'll still be less than the

00:32:07.812 --> 00:32:08.370
velocity of light.

00:32:13.950 --> 00:32:17.522
And the last thing you want to
check of this velocity addition

00:32:17.522 --> 00:32:20.099
formula is why we started the
whole thing.

00:32:20.099 --> 00:32:23.410
In other words,
suppose I see a pulse of light.

00:32:23.410 --> 00:32:26.690
Let's go back now to this
formula.

00:32:26.690 --> 00:32:32.660
w is v - u over 1
- uv over c^(2).

00:32:32.660 --> 00:32:35.626
Rather than applying it to a
bullet or whatnot,

00:32:35.626 --> 00:32:38.400
let's apply it to the light
pulse itself.

00:32:38.400 --> 00:32:42.784
So, I saw a light pulse so I
say the object I saw,

00:32:42.784 --> 00:32:47.436
which is what v stands
for, had a value

00:32:47.436 --> 00:32:51.461
c.
And this is the pre-Einstein

00:32:51.461 --> 00:32:54.637
expectation.
w should be c - u

00:32:54.637 --> 00:32:58.214
because the pulse appears to
travel slower to a person moving

00:32:58.214 --> 00:33:00.480
in the same direction as the
pulse.

00:33:00.480 --> 00:33:05.788
But our new formula says it is
really that uc over

00:33:05.788 --> 00:33:07.210
c^(2).

00:33:10.460 --> 00:33:14.115
So, that canceled one part of
c, multiply top and

00:33:14.115 --> 00:33:16.906
bottom by c,
and you will find it is

00:33:16.906 --> 00:33:19.749
c.
So, the velocity of light will

00:33:19.749 --> 00:33:23.282
always come out to be the same.
That is built into the formula

00:33:23.282 --> 00:33:27.020
but it is a good thing to test.
So, what you find is,

00:33:27.020 --> 00:33:31.250
velocities don't add in the
simple way.

00:33:31.250 --> 00:33:34.214
If they did, you are in trouble.
You cannot get an upper limit

00:33:34.214 --> 00:33:37.012
if they added in the simple way
because you can put a rocket

00:33:37.012 --> 00:33:39.714
inside another rocket inside
another rocket and add up all

00:33:39.714 --> 00:33:42.369
the speeds and even though each
one is less than 0,

00:33:42.369 --> 00:33:44.050
the total could be whatever you
like.

00:33:44.050 --> 00:33:47.460
But they don't add that way.
They add this way so that the

00:33:47.460 --> 00:33:50.520
answer is either bigger than
what you think if v and

00:33:50.520 --> 00:33:53.547
u are opposite,
or smaller than what you think

00:33:53.547 --> 00:33:56.450
if the velocities in the top are
of the same sign.

00:33:56.450 --> 00:33:59.424
No matter what you do,
the answer will always be less

00:33:59.424 --> 00:34:03.519
than c.
Okay, so that is the first

00:34:03.519 --> 00:34:08.724
conclusion from this.
Second conclusion,

00:34:08.724 --> 00:34:16.826
which is again very staggering,
is that simultaneity is the

00:34:16.826 --> 00:34:20.490
relative concept.
In other words,

00:34:20.490 --> 00:34:24.148
if two events occur at the same
time for me, they don't occur at

00:34:24.148 --> 00:34:27.440
the same time for you.
That is very surprising.

00:34:27.440 --> 00:34:30.187
For example,
if you have twins born,

00:34:30.187 --> 00:34:33.797
one in New-- sorry,
twins cannot be born in New

00:34:33.797 --> 00:34:38.118
York and Los Angeles.
So, I've got to pick two kids

00:34:38.118 --> 00:34:42.592
of different motherhood,
just happened to be born at the

00:34:42.592 --> 00:34:44.880
same time.
When I say "time," we're not

00:34:44.880 --> 00:34:47.474
talking about trivial three-hour
time difference between Los

00:34:47.474 --> 00:34:50.039
Angeles and New York.
That's an artificial thing.

00:34:50.039 --> 00:34:51.498
In the Einstein world,
you imagine,

00:34:51.498 --> 00:34:53.429
we all have clocks that read
the same time.

00:34:53.429 --> 00:34:56.718
So, by that measure,
the two kids are born at the

00:34:56.718 --> 00:35:00.966
same time but if you watch that
from a moving train or a moving

00:35:00.966 --> 00:35:03.570
rocket, you will disagree on
that.

00:35:03.570 --> 00:35:06.630
You will, in fact,
say they are not simultaneous.

00:35:06.630 --> 00:35:09.012
How does that come?
Well, it just comes from going

00:35:09.012 --> 00:35:12.544
to this formula.
Δt prime is Δt -

00:35:12.544 --> 00:35:18.334
uΔa x over c^(2)
divided by this number and all

00:35:18.334 --> 00:35:23.243
I'm telling you is,
even though Δt is 0,

00:35:23.243 --> 00:35:28.440
Δt prime is not 0.
Another shock.

00:35:28.440 --> 00:35:34.530
Simultaneity is not absolute.
We used to think it's absolute.

00:35:34.530 --> 00:35:37.449
In other words,
two events are occurring in Los

00:35:37.449 --> 00:35:40.723
Angeles and New York.
They can be arranged to be

00:35:40.723 --> 00:35:43.583
simultaneous for me,
living on the planet,

00:35:43.583 --> 00:35:45.764
let's say,
but if you go in a rocket,

00:35:45.764 --> 00:35:48.019
I expect you to agree they were
simultaneous.

00:35:48.019 --> 00:35:49.840
I mean, how can they be
different?

00:35:49.840 --> 00:35:52.509
Two things are happening right
now in different places,

00:35:52.509 --> 00:35:54.240
it's got to be right now for
you.

00:35:54.240 --> 00:35:56.949
But it's not.
It just comes from that formula.

00:35:56.949 --> 00:36:00.379
Once again, if the velocity of
light is made much bigger than

00:36:00.379 --> 00:36:03.855
everything in the problem,
simply to set it to infinity,

00:36:03.855 --> 00:36:06.829
you will find Δt prime
is Δt.

00:36:06.829 --> 00:36:12.111
That goes back to Galilean
times or the old pre-Einstein

00:36:12.111 --> 00:36:14.943
times.
That's why in relativity,

00:36:14.943 --> 00:36:19.565
space and time form a new
space-time and time is called a

00:36:19.565 --> 00:36:24.269
fourth component because if
c goes to infinity,

00:36:24.269 --> 00:36:27.119
Δ prime is always
Δt and t prime is

00:36:27.119 --> 00:36:29.292
always t.
If the coordinate never mixes

00:36:29.292 --> 00:36:31.487
with anything else,
it doesn't deserve to be called

00:36:31.487 --> 00:36:33.496
a coordinate,
whereas, it's the x and

00:36:33.496 --> 00:36:35.934
y coordinates that mix
with each other when you do

00:36:35.934 --> 00:36:37.466
rotations.
After Einstein,

00:36:37.466 --> 00:36:41.398
the space and time coordinates
mix with each other to give you

00:36:41.398 --> 00:36:45.460
new space and time coordinates
under Lorentz transformation,

00:36:45.460 --> 00:36:48.309
which means,
when seen in a moving train.

00:36:48.309 --> 00:36:52.644
That's why time is now elevated
to another dimension because it

00:36:52.644 --> 00:36:56.630
transforms very much the way
x and y did.

00:36:56.630 --> 00:36:58.329
The details of the
transformation are different.

00:36:58.329 --> 00:37:01.062
We have sines and cosines
replaced by u and

00:37:01.062 --> 00:37:04.297
u over the square root
but it's still mathematically

00:37:04.297 --> 00:37:07.030
the way components of vectors
will transform.

00:37:07.030 --> 00:37:09.340
Okay, so simultaneity is
relative.

00:37:09.340 --> 00:37:14.679
So, you have to ask yourself,
"How did that happen?"

00:37:14.679 --> 00:37:18.059
So, here's the famous example
that is given in all the books.

00:37:18.059 --> 00:37:20.360
Maybe it was given by Einstein,
I'm not sure.

00:37:20.360 --> 00:37:21.530
So, here's a train.

00:37:24.550 --> 00:37:28.190
Let's say the train is at rest
and you are standing in the

00:37:28.190 --> 00:37:31.384
middle and you want to arrange
for two events to be

00:37:31.384 --> 00:37:33.659
simultaneous.
Oh by the way,

00:37:33.659 --> 00:37:38.650
there is one catch.
If the two events occurred at

00:37:38.650 --> 00:37:44.097
the same time and the same
place, Δx = 0,

00:37:44.097 --> 00:37:47.360
Δt = 0;
then, the transformation will

00:37:47.360 --> 00:37:49.800
tell you Δx prime is 0
and Δt prime is 0.

00:37:49.800 --> 00:37:53.158
Because two events occurring at
the same time,

00:37:53.158 --> 00:37:56.070
at the same place means,
for example,

00:37:56.070 --> 00:37:58.907
my two hands came and clapped,
the two hands were at the same

00:37:58.907 --> 00:38:00.861
time at the same place.
If someone said,

00:38:00.861 --> 00:38:03.466
well, they were not at the same
place at the same time,

00:38:03.466 --> 00:38:06.889
it means I didn't clap.
Two cars collide.

00:38:06.889 --> 00:38:10.288
So, if two things occur at the
same time at the same place,

00:38:10.288 --> 00:38:13.159
something happened that they
met in space-time.

00:38:13.159 --> 00:38:16.304
You cannot find another
observer who says they did not

00:38:16.304 --> 00:38:19.270
meet in space-time,
or they'll say the two cars did

00:38:19.270 --> 00:38:21.911
not collide.
Even after relativity,

00:38:21.911 --> 00:38:26.294
it is true that two events at
the same time and same place

00:38:26.294 --> 00:38:30.369
occur the same time and same
place for all people.

00:38:30.369 --> 00:38:36.262
Same time alone is not enough
and same place alone is not

00:38:36.262 --> 00:38:38.340
enough.
You see that?

00:38:38.340 --> 00:38:41.368
If two cars came and they
collided, they were at the same

00:38:41.368 --> 00:38:44.503
time at the same place.
If the cars were at the same

00:38:44.503 --> 00:38:47.179
time, here and there,
that's no accident.

00:38:47.179 --> 00:38:49.923
If they were at the same place
because if this car went and two

00:38:49.923 --> 00:38:51.914
minutes later that car went at
the same place,

00:38:51.914 --> 00:38:54.892
nothing happens.
That's why you say this poor

00:38:54.892 --> 00:38:58.329
guy was in the wrong place at
the wrong time.

00:38:58.329 --> 00:39:00.540
You don't want to say this guy
was in the wrong place.

00:39:00.540 --> 00:39:02.751
What does that mean?
You can go to the Battle of

00:39:02.751 --> 00:39:05.240
Gettysburg site and stand now
and nothing happens to you

00:39:05.240 --> 00:39:07.730
because it's the same place but
it's the wrong time.

00:39:07.730 --> 00:39:09.393
Okay?
We all realize,

00:39:09.393 --> 00:39:12.160
same place, same time,
is a congruence in space-time

00:39:12.160 --> 00:39:14.981
and even after Einstein,
you cannot say something did

00:39:14.981 --> 00:39:16.860
not happen.
Okay.

00:39:16.860 --> 00:39:18.780
We leave that to politicians
please.

00:39:18.780 --> 00:39:21.784
It did happen.
It still happened and the

00:39:21.784 --> 00:39:25.250
equations have the property but
I've got several events

00:39:25.250 --> 00:39:28.010
separated in space but at the
same time.

00:39:28.010 --> 00:39:30.543
You're in the train.
Your job is to make two things

00:39:30.543 --> 00:39:33.030
happen at the same time and
here's what you do.

00:39:33.030 --> 00:39:36.353
You send a beam of light that
splits into a,

00:39:36.353 --> 00:39:39.289
you know, here's a blown up
picture.

00:39:39.289 --> 00:39:42.374
Beam of light comes and splits
like that and goes to the back

00:39:42.374 --> 00:39:45.022
and front of the train.
You're in the middle of the

00:39:45.022 --> 00:39:48.150
train, and you know that events
will be simultaneous for you.

00:39:48.150 --> 00:39:51.987
The pulse travels on either
side and hits the two things at

00:39:51.987 --> 00:39:56.022
the two ends and sets off two
explosions and you have done the

00:39:56.022 --> 00:39:59.000
best you can to have
simultaneous events.

00:39:59.000 --> 00:40:03.619
Okay now, I see you from the
ground.

00:40:03.619 --> 00:40:05.854
So, all this happening in the
moving train,

00:40:05.854 --> 00:40:08.568
you have every right to say
you're not moving but to

00:40:08.568 --> 00:40:10.590
me--relative to me you are
moving.

00:40:10.590 --> 00:40:13.002
That's a fact.
And I look at how well you did

00:40:13.002 --> 00:40:15.889
with this.
So, you sent off these two

00:40:15.889 --> 00:40:18.329
light pulses.
Then what happened?

00:40:18.329 --> 00:40:21.727
This wall of the train is
moving away from the light

00:40:21.727 --> 00:40:23.324
pulse.
This wall of the train,

00:40:23.324 --> 00:40:25.223
the rear end,
is rushing to meet the light

00:40:25.223 --> 00:40:27.869
pulse.
Now, the velocity of light is

00:40:27.869 --> 00:40:32.789
the same for everybody so I can
think in terms of what happens.

00:40:32.789 --> 00:40:35.450
If one wall is rushing to meet
the light pulse and one wall is

00:40:35.450 --> 00:40:37.019
running away from the light
pulse,

00:40:37.019 --> 00:40:39.690
I know very clearly the
firecracker in the back of the

00:40:39.690 --> 00:40:42.714
train will go off first and in
the front of the train will go

00:40:42.714 --> 00:40:47.533
off later.
That means that Δt will

00:40:47.533 --> 00:40:50.794
not be 0.
In fact, you can see Δt

00:40:50.794 --> 00:40:54.475
will be negative because the
event with the greater x

00:40:54.475 --> 00:40:58.485
coordinate occurs later.
That's also an agreement of the

00:40:58.485 --> 00:41:00.052
formula.
If Δt = 0,

00:41:00.052 --> 00:41:02.630
then Δx prime will be
some negative number.

00:41:05.869 --> 00:41:07.719
Now, why do we bring in the
light pulse?

00:41:07.719 --> 00:41:10.890
We bring in the light pulse
because we can tell that they

00:41:10.890 --> 00:41:14.230
were simply not simultaneous
because about the light we know

00:41:14.230 --> 00:41:16.147
this.
Its velocity is the same for

00:41:16.147 --> 00:41:18.240
everybody.
That's why all arguments in

00:41:18.240 --> 00:41:21.150
relativity involve doing things
with light pulses or

00:41:21.150 --> 00:41:25.030
communicating with a light pulse
because we know what light does.

00:41:25.030 --> 00:41:27.780
It travels at one and the same
velocity for all people.

00:41:27.780 --> 00:41:31.047
That's a postulate.
Therefore, we know you couldn't

00:41:31.047 --> 00:41:35.553
have done any better in making
them simultaneous and I simply

00:41:35.553 --> 00:41:38.500
disagree with you.
I'd say they just did not

00:41:38.500 --> 00:41:41.461
happen at the same time,
and there's no question of who

00:41:41.461 --> 00:41:43.062
is right.
Operationally,

00:41:43.062 --> 00:41:47.168
for me, those two events were
separated in time by some amount

00:41:47.168 --> 00:41:50.876
and for you they were not.
That's a great new idea that

00:41:50.876 --> 00:41:54.139
things did not happen the same
time for all people,

00:41:54.139 --> 00:41:57.079
and relativity tells you that
they didn't and tells you by how

00:41:57.079 --> 00:42:00.739
much they were different.
Okay.

00:42:00.739 --> 00:42:03.739
Then, I take the next surprise
here.

00:42:03.739 --> 00:42:06.130
The next surprise has to do
with clocks.

00:42:09.860 --> 00:42:12.519
The claim is that clocks will
not run at the same rate.

00:42:12.519 --> 00:42:14.981
Okay, when we bought the
clocks, we compared them,

00:42:14.981 --> 00:42:18.333
we got them from the same shop,
they were completely in synch

00:42:18.333 --> 00:42:21.837
and you put one in your train
and you got into your train and

00:42:21.837 --> 00:42:25.166
the claim is that I will find
that your clocks are running

00:42:25.166 --> 00:42:29.300
slow.
Let me show that to you.

00:42:29.300 --> 00:42:31.973
Again, if you want to do
anything with relativity,

00:42:31.973 --> 00:42:34.734
at least learn this one thing.
Go back to Lorentz

00:42:34.734 --> 00:42:37.890
transformation and think in
terms of events that are just

00:42:37.890 --> 00:42:41.306
going to come out of the wash.
If you try something original

00:42:41.306 --> 00:42:43.829
on your own, you people do all
kinds of stuff.

00:42:43.829 --> 00:42:46.257
I've seen you going in a
cyclical circular or arguments

00:42:46.257 --> 00:42:49.180
from which you cannot even come
out until somebody rescues you.

00:42:49.180 --> 00:42:52.139
So don't do that.
So, I'm looking at a clock.

00:42:52.139 --> 00:42:56.095
You've got to ask yourself,
how do I turn this issue of

00:42:56.095 --> 00:42:59.820
time into a pair of events?
I have my clock,

00:42:59.820 --> 00:43:03.120
so it goes tick-tock,
tick-tock.

00:43:03.120 --> 00:43:08.156
I pick two events.
Event 1: a clock says tick,

00:43:08.156 --> 00:43:12.320
and event 2:
clock says tock.

00:43:12.320 --> 00:43:15.458
I tell you why I have tick and
tock because I want to have two

00:43:15.458 --> 00:43:18.340
distant kind of events so that
we can talk about them.

00:43:18.340 --> 00:43:22.650
So, this event is a clock that
I'm carrying with me.

00:43:22.650 --> 00:43:27.338
The clock is with me.
So, let me put a clock at the

00:43:27.338 --> 00:43:30.060
center of my coordinates system
or the origin.

00:43:30.060 --> 00:43:32.750
It doesn't matter where it is.
Let me put it at the origin.

00:43:32.750 --> 00:43:36.851
The space-time coordinate x
= 0, t = 0 is the

00:43:36.851 --> 00:43:38.690
first tick of the clock.

00:43:41.930 --> 00:43:45.288
How about the next tick?
The next tick,

00:43:45.288 --> 00:43:49.514
this is x and t
coordinates, the tock of the

00:43:49.514 --> 00:43:52.924
clock, let me call
τ_0 is the

00:43:52.924 --> 00:43:55.590
time of the clock.
It's a time period;

00:43:55.590 --> 00:43:59.719
how many seconds elapsed
between the tick and the tock.

00:43:59.719 --> 00:44:03.805
The main question is,
"What is the location of the

00:44:03.805 --> 00:44:07.480
second tick of the clock?"
Where does that happen?

00:44:07.480 --> 00:44:10.298
Yes?
Student:

00:44:10.298 --> 00:44:11.461
[inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:44:11.461 --> 00:44:13.364
Shankar: It doesn't move
with respect to me and I'm

00:44:13.364 --> 00:44:15.408
talking about a clock that I'm
holding in my hand so if the

00:44:15.408 --> 00:44:17.030
first event took place at x
= 0,

00:44:17.030 --> 00:44:19.730
second one also takes place at
x = 0.

00:44:19.730 --> 00:44:21.250
You understand?
I'm holding the clock.

00:44:21.250 --> 00:44:24.518
I've traveled forward in time.
It's τ_0

00:44:24.518 --> 00:44:27.418
seconds later but the clock has
not gone anywhere so the two

00:44:27.418 --> 00:44:29.531
events,
the two tickings of the clock,

00:44:29.531 --> 00:44:31.748
are separated in space by 0 and
in time by

00:44:31.748 --> 00:44:35.389
τ_0.
That means Δx =

00:44:35.389 --> 00:44:39.970
0, Δt =
τ_0.

00:44:39.970 --> 00:44:42.694
What do you get?
According to you,

00:44:42.694 --> 00:44:46.526
the time difference between the
two ticks is Δt,

00:44:46.526 --> 00:44:50.010
which is τ_0
- u etc.,

00:44:50.010 --> 00:44:54.810
times 0 divided by this factor.
So, that means the time

00:44:54.810 --> 00:44:59.179
difference between the two ticks
would be bigger.

00:44:59.179 --> 00:45:02.385
If τ_0 is 1
second, if you divide 1 by [root

00:45:02.385 --> 00:45:04.329
of]
1 - u^(2) over c^(2),

00:45:04.329 --> 00:45:06.880
 you're going to find out
it is less.

00:45:06.880 --> 00:45:09.393
There's more.
For example,

00:45:09.393 --> 00:45:12.815
if this factor in the
denominator is .5,

00:45:12.815 --> 00:45:17.818
then Δt would be 2
times τ_0. In

00:45:17.818 --> 00:45:20.778
other words,
when your clock has taken 1

00:45:20.778 --> 00:45:24.203
second to go from 1 tick to the
next, I will say according to me

00:45:24.203 --> 00:45:26.269
the real time elapsed is 2
seconds.

00:45:26.269 --> 00:45:28.750
It can be 10 seconds,
it can 100 seconds.

00:45:28.750 --> 00:45:31.491
You can make Δt as big
as you like by letting you

00:45:31.491 --> 00:45:32.470
approach c.

00:45:38.270 --> 00:45:39.583
Yes?
Student:

00:45:39.583 --> 00:45:40.755
[inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:45:40.755 --> 00:45:43.890
Shankar: Thank you.
I'm having this problem today

00:45:43.890 --> 00:45:46.415
with the prime.
t prime is

00:45:46.415 --> 00:45:49.366
τ_0 over this.
If you put

00:45:49.366 --> 00:45:50.990
τ_0,
I put 1 second.

00:45:50.990 --> 00:45:54.559
Question there, guys?
Student:

00:45:54.559 --> 00:45:57.199
[inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:45:57.199 --> 00:46:00.800
Shankar: No,
u did not go to 0.

00:46:00.800 --> 00:46:04.883
u is not 0.
uΔx over c^(2,)

00:46:04.883 --> 00:46:07.440
it is the Δx that went
to 0.

00:46:07.440 --> 00:46:13.465
Go the Lorentz transformation.
Δt prime is Δt -

00:46:13.465 --> 00:46:19.199
uΔx over c^(2).
Δx = 0.

00:46:19.199 --> 00:46:24.549
That's where I'm telling the
equation the clock is at rest

00:46:24.549 --> 00:46:27.358
with respect to me.
That means that--

00:46:27.358 --> 00:46:28.641
Student:
[inaudible]

00:46:28.641 --> 00:46:30.515
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: No,

00:46:30.515 --> 00:46:32.032
no.
In this example,

00:46:32.032 --> 00:46:35.960
let the unprimed observer be
the one holding the clock.

00:46:35.960 --> 00:46:38.615
Then Δx is,
you know Δt is whatever

00:46:38.615 --> 00:46:40.909
the time of the clock is.
1 second.

00:46:40.909 --> 00:46:43.962
Δt prime is seen by
anybody else going at a speed

00:46:43.962 --> 00:46:46.989
u relative to me.
You can also do it backwards by

00:46:46.989 --> 00:46:50.158
taking the clock in the hands of
the S prime but you've

00:46:50.158 --> 00:46:53.344
got to do a little more work.
It's a lot easier here because

00:46:53.344 --> 00:46:56.139
I get to pump into the equation
two facts at one shot,

00:46:56.139 --> 00:46:59.882
that the time between the two
ticks is 1 second and it's at

00:46:59.882 --> 00:47:03.193
rest with respect to me,
which is why the Δx

00:47:03.193 --> 00:47:06.231
vanished between the two ticks.
If I want to use your

00:47:06.231 --> 00:47:09.324
equations, Δx prime
won't be 0 because the clock has

00:47:09.324 --> 00:47:11.754
moved and you can do it.
I've, I think,

00:47:11.754 --> 00:47:15.740
shown in my notes how to do
that but it's unnecessary.

00:47:15.740 --> 00:47:18.929
This is the main result.
Now, here is the paradox.

00:47:18.929 --> 00:47:22.350
You can go back to the
backwards equations.

00:47:22.350 --> 00:47:27.990
Let's do this informally, okay.
Let's not write it again.

00:47:27.990 --> 00:47:30.950
It will look like this.
Right.

00:47:30.950 --> 00:47:33.093
You know that.
Let's take a clock you are

00:47:33.093 --> 00:47:35.134
carrying.
It ticks off 1 second,

00:47:35.134 --> 00:47:38.954
so between the tick and the
next tick, the time difference

00:47:38.954 --> 00:47:41.318
is 1 second,
space difference is 0,

00:47:41.318 --> 00:47:44.159
I'll find Δt is 1 over
a square root.

00:47:44.159 --> 00:47:47.137
So, I will say your clock is
slow, you'll say my clock is

00:47:47.137 --> 00:47:50.860
slow.
How is that possible?

00:47:50.860 --> 00:47:54.739
How can it be that we accuse
each other of having--yes?

00:47:54.739 --> 00:47:57.520
Student:
[inaudible]

00:47:57.520 --> 00:48:01.585
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Oh,

00:48:01.585 --> 00:48:05.931
you're absolutely right.
The predictions are in

00:48:05.931 --> 00:48:09.496
agreement with that principle,
but I ask you to think about

00:48:09.496 --> 00:48:11.340
the conflict you have,
yes?

00:48:11.340 --> 00:48:13.835
Student:
[inaudible]

00:48:13.835 --> 00:48:17.483
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Oh,

00:48:17.483 --> 00:48:20.366
that's very good.
Student:

00:48:20.366 --> 00:48:22.271
[inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:48:22.271 --> 00:48:24.350
Shankar: No,
that is correct.

00:48:24.350 --> 00:48:27.034
Let me repeat what he said.
He said, if there are two

00:48:27.034 --> 00:48:29.967
people, they were right next to
each other, they are at the same

00:48:29.967 --> 00:48:32.761
height and they move apart and
each person looks at the other

00:48:32.761 --> 00:48:35.368
person and finds the person
diminished in size because of

00:48:35.368 --> 00:48:37.834
the distance,
and each person can tell the

00:48:37.834 --> 00:48:40.300
other person you look small from
where I am.

00:48:40.300 --> 00:48:43.499
In fact, even more paradoxical
is how in this world two people

00:48:43.499 --> 00:48:45.860
can simultaneously look down on
each other.

00:48:45.860 --> 00:48:48.616
You figure that out.
There are two people who

00:48:48.616 --> 00:48:51.713
simultaneously have higher
opinion of themselves to the

00:48:51.713 --> 00:48:55.039
other person and are the same
thing, they look down on each

00:48:55.039 --> 00:48:57.059
other.
I have not found how many space

00:48:57.059 --> 00:48:59.613
dimensions I should embed but
these people to make it that

00:48:59.613 --> 00:49:01.539
possible, but this is certainly
correct.

00:49:01.539 --> 00:49:04.340
A spatial resolution does give
the impression.

00:49:04.340 --> 00:49:07.621
So, here's the answer that's
usually given to explain this to

00:49:07.621 --> 00:49:09.914
you.
If I take a real clock like

00:49:09.914 --> 00:49:14.062
this watch here and I ask you
why does it look slow to you

00:49:14.062 --> 00:49:18.378
when I'm moving relative to you,
it's difficult because it's got

00:49:18.378 --> 00:49:21.686
electronics and stuff and I
still don't know how to set the

00:49:21.686 --> 00:49:24.025
clock on my VCR.
I'm not going to figure that

00:49:24.025 --> 00:49:25.927
out.
So, for all of us guys who are

00:49:25.927 --> 00:49:29.004
challenged, there is a clock
that's particularly simple,

00:49:29.004 --> 00:49:33.821
and the clock works like this.
It has got two mirrors and a

00:49:33.821 --> 00:49:39.764
light pulse just goes up and
down between the mirrors and

00:49:39.764 --> 00:49:44.010
every time it completes a round
trip,

00:49:44.010 --> 00:49:46.849
it sets off some detector and
it goes "click."

00:49:46.849 --> 00:49:50.676
Now, this is very important to
mention that this is my x

00:49:50.676 --> 00:49:54.010
coordinate and that's the
y coordinate and I did

00:49:54.010 --> 00:49:57.590
not show you here there are
logical arguments and why,

00:49:57.590 --> 00:50:00.154
if you and I are moving along
x, why our y

00:50:00.154 --> 00:50:02.300
coordinates, if they agree in
the beginning,

00:50:02.300 --> 00:50:05.183
continue to agree.
That's because if you say

00:50:05.183 --> 00:50:07.925
something is two meters tall and
they pass each other,

00:50:07.925 --> 00:50:11.132
you cannot have a disagreement
on the fact that heights are the

00:50:11.132 --> 00:50:13.089
same.
But as in a linear dimension

00:50:13.089 --> 00:50:15.968
there is room for discussion,
in the transverse dimension

00:50:15.968 --> 00:50:18.279
there isn't.
So, anyway, I have this clock

00:50:18.279 --> 00:50:21.340
that goes up and down.
Light pulse goes up and down.

00:50:21.340 --> 00:50:24.717
It goes a certain distance,
L, in a vertical

00:50:24.717 --> 00:50:28.769
direction, and 2L/c is
the time period of my clock.

00:50:28.769 --> 00:50:30.840
That's the time for a round
trip.

00:50:30.840 --> 00:50:35.170
You look at my clock and what
do you think is happening?

00:50:35.170 --> 00:50:38.517
Remember, you are moving to the
right, relative to me,

00:50:38.517 --> 00:50:41.674
so according to you my clock is
moving to the left,

00:50:41.674 --> 00:50:43.380
and it looks like this.

00:50:47.369 --> 00:50:51.790
Light beam is going on a zigzag
path, according to you.

00:50:51.790 --> 00:50:55.091
You agree that's very clear.
For me, the pulse is going up

00:50:55.091 --> 00:50:57.989
and down, for you it's going on
the hypotenuse.

00:50:57.989 --> 00:51:01.255
You can imagine how with the
hypotenuse u^(2) and

00:51:01.255 --> 00:51:04.758
c^(2) are going to come
from drawing the sides of the

00:51:04.758 --> 00:51:07.215
triangle.
That's why the time would come

00:51:07.215 --> 00:51:10.655
out longer.
Now, why do they like this

00:51:10.655 --> 00:51:12.596
clock?
Because we know everything

00:51:12.596 --> 00:51:14.159
about the operation of the
clock.

00:51:14.159 --> 00:51:18.802
We know that this path is
longer than the straight up and

00:51:18.802 --> 00:51:23.860
down path because the transfers'
coordinate is known to us.

00:51:23.860 --> 00:51:25.605
Furthermore,
we know the velocity of light

00:51:25.605 --> 00:51:27.349
is the same in all frames of
reference;

00:51:27.349 --> 00:51:30.254
so, light going on a longer
path is simply going to take

00:51:30.254 --> 00:51:33.856
longer.
So, I know your clock would

00:51:33.856 --> 00:51:36.239
slow down.
Now, here is the beauty.

00:51:36.239 --> 00:51:38.762
The beauty is that,
if you have a clock that's

00:51:38.762 --> 00:51:40.949
going up and down,
straight up and down,

00:51:40.949 --> 00:51:43.640
when I see it,
it's going to look like this.

00:51:48.000 --> 00:51:50.740
So, it's as simple as saying
that if you had these two

00:51:50.740 --> 00:51:53.895
clocks, what I think is going up
and down and you think it's a

00:51:53.895 --> 00:51:56.252
zigzag this way,
and I look at your clock,

00:51:56.252 --> 00:51:59.269
it's a zigzag the other way,
it's perfectly okay for me to

00:51:59.269 --> 00:52:01.550
say to you,
your light pulse is going on a

00:52:01.550 --> 00:52:04.631
hypotenuse and mine is going up
and down, and why you can say

00:52:04.631 --> 00:52:08.217
that to me.
So, at least this light clock

00:52:08.217 --> 00:52:13.260
explains to you why clocks will
appear to be slow.

00:52:13.260 --> 00:52:16.544
Now, the question you can ask
is, what if I have some other

00:52:16.544 --> 00:52:19.490
clock with gears and wheels and
teeth and whatnot?

00:52:19.490 --> 00:52:21.948
How does that slow down?
The answer is,

00:52:21.948 --> 00:52:26.500
we don't know exactly how to
explain that clock but I know

00:52:26.500 --> 00:52:31.532
that if you carry a light clock
and another clock made of wheels

00:52:31.532 --> 00:52:34.513
and gears,
they should run at the same

00:52:34.513 --> 00:52:36.584
rate.
They should run at the same

00:52:36.584 --> 00:52:39.251
rate because if they ran at
different rates,

00:52:39.251 --> 00:52:43.255
one slowed down and one didn't,
in comparing the two clocks you

00:52:43.255 --> 00:52:46.801
can determine your velocity,
and that we know is impossible

00:52:46.801 --> 00:52:50.469
by the postulate that you cannot
detect uniform velocity.

00:52:50.469 --> 00:52:53.666
Therefore, if the light clock
does something,

00:52:53.666 --> 00:52:57.444
all clocks must do the same
thing regardless of their

00:52:57.444 --> 00:53:01.150
mechanism, and that includes
biological clocks.

00:53:01.150 --> 00:53:05.001
So, if you have a clock which
is just yourself,

00:53:05.001 --> 00:53:08.770
I look at you,
you know, over 15 or 20 years I

00:53:08.770 --> 00:53:11.714
notice some changes.
You become taller,

00:53:11.714 --> 00:53:14.260
then your hair turns white,
your teeth fall off.

00:53:14.260 --> 00:53:17.889
That's a clock and that clock
should also slow down.

00:53:17.889 --> 00:53:21.284
I don't care how your life
systems work but you are a clock

00:53:21.284 --> 00:53:24.280
and you've got to slow down.
That's why we can make

00:53:24.280 --> 00:53:27.665
predictions about what happened
to living systems even though

00:53:27.665 --> 00:53:30.460
that's not our main business.
So, in particular,

00:53:30.460 --> 00:53:33.213
if you take a clock,
which is made up of mechanical

00:53:33.213 --> 00:53:36.751
parts and a human being,
and they travel at high speeds,

00:53:36.751 --> 00:53:40.590
the aging of the human being
should slow down just like the

00:53:40.590 --> 00:53:43.039
clock's ticking will slow it
down,

00:53:43.039 --> 00:53:44.880
without knowing the reasons for
it.

00:53:44.880 --> 00:53:48.280
So, this leads to a very famous
paradox called the Twin Paradox.

00:53:48.280 --> 00:53:53.322
The Twin Paradox says that
you've got two guys,

00:53:53.322 --> 00:53:56.191
twins.
Now, this is actually a valid

00:53:56.191 --> 00:53:58.243
example.
They were born at the same

00:53:58.243 --> 00:54:00.891
time, same place,
and then the one goes on a trip

00:54:00.891 --> 00:54:04.090
at some speed u,
and goes around and comes back.

00:54:04.090 --> 00:54:08.740
So, I think the person's been
gone for 20 years,

00:54:08.740 --> 00:54:11.655
my twin.
So, let's say he was 20 when he

00:54:11.655 --> 00:54:14.760
left, so I expect him to be 40
when he gets back.

00:54:14.760 --> 00:54:19.208
But he'll come back younger
because as a clock,

00:54:19.208 --> 00:54:23.400
he has slowed down.
So, what I think is 20 years,

00:54:23.400 --> 00:54:25.932
this could be,
my time is 20 years,

00:54:25.932 --> 00:54:30.104
but his time could be 10
because his factor downstairs is

00:54:30.104 --> 00:54:33.052
.5.
So, he can come back being

00:54:33.052 --> 00:54:35.719
younger than me.
Yes?

00:54:35.719 --> 00:54:38.236
Student:
[inaudible]

00:54:38.236 --> 00:54:41.913
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Oh,

00:54:41.913 --> 00:54:46.329
but we've got to be careful.
So, his point had something to

00:54:46.329 --> 00:54:48.659
do with acceleration,
but the real question is this.

00:54:48.659 --> 00:54:52.833
See, if I'm on the ground and I
send my twin on the trip and we

00:54:52.833 --> 00:54:55.659
meet, now the clocks are being
compared.

00:54:55.659 --> 00:54:58.081
As long as the zigzag is going
this way and that zigzag is

00:54:58.081 --> 00:54:59.949
going that way,
you can say what you like.

00:54:59.949 --> 00:55:02.146
But what if the clocks are
brought head-to-head and

00:55:02.146 --> 00:55:04.604
compared?
Can they both be slower than

00:55:04.604 --> 00:55:06.840
the other?
We know that's impossible.

00:55:06.840 --> 00:55:09.355
So, instead of clocks,
we use human beings and

00:55:09.355 --> 00:55:12.429
dramatize the paradox and say,
"Who will be younger?"

00:55:12.429 --> 00:55:14.140
Me or the twin who went on the
rocket?

00:55:17.460 --> 00:55:20.249
Well, there can only be one
answer to that question,

00:55:20.249 --> 00:55:23.312
and yet no matter what the twin
says, I have no reason to

00:55:23.312 --> 00:55:26.030
believe that I moved.
You are the one who went on the

00:55:26.030 --> 00:55:28.600
trip the opposite way so you've
got to be younger than me.

00:55:28.600 --> 00:55:32.230
Yes?
Student:

00:55:32.230 --> 00:55:38.634
[inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:55:38.634 --> 00:55:44.240
Shankar: Very good.
Okay.

00:55:44.240 --> 00:55:46.139
I couldn't have said it better.
Let me repeat it.

00:55:46.139 --> 00:55:47.698
The point is,
as long as you've got

00:55:47.698 --> 00:55:50.264
oppositely moving clocks,
they can believe what they want

00:55:50.264 --> 00:55:53.105
of each other,
but if you want the clocks to

00:55:53.105 --> 00:55:56.789
be subject to a comparison,
then you can never compare

